      "dateCreated": "",
      "description": "AptaSelect identifies high-frequency aptamer candidate sequences from paired-end FASTQ files generated by SELEX experiments. It processes reads through five stages: paired-end joining, selection filtering, 1st sort filtering, 2nd sort filtering, and aggregation & ranking. Pattern matching tolerates user-defined mismatches, and processing is parallelised across configurable read chunks. The final output is a ranked TSV of the top-N most enriched aptamer core sequences.",
